        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Noah_C\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"322150\" data-full=\"true\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/noah_c/48/3440_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Noah_C:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Never had the grand vin myself. Can you comment on how this compares? Obviously not the same caliber, but is the character similar? Does it taste like it belongs in at least the same stable as the flagship Lafleur?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/marc_frontario\">@Marc_Frontario</a> is bringing a 1993 Lafleur to a dinner party at my house on the 24th, will let you know!  Marx is the king of finding gems in so-called off-vintages!</p>",
