      {
        "id": 4370203,
        "name": "Chris Kissack",
        "username": "Chris_Kissack",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/chris_kissack/{size}/270050_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-05-16T12:37:13.172Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Very good call on Les Perri\u00e8res, it\u2019s a wine I adore, and I think it was a smart move by them to rechristen it Les Perri\u00e8res instead of Acte.</p>\n<p>The name is very appropriate as <em>perri\u00e8res</em> refers to a stone quarry (I think this has been discussed on WB before) and there is indeed an old quarry beneath some of the vineyards, with a number of vertical shafts among the vines. When the Guinaudeau family acquired the vineyard a number of these shafts were still open/uncovered - Baptiste Guinaudeau was exploring the vines for the first time and came close to falling down one.</p>\n<p>He subsequently had them secured with metal gratings! <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/astonished.png?v=12\" title=\":astonished:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":astonished:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/astonished.png?v=12\" title=\":astonished:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":astonished:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>Both 2019 and 2020 are super wines.</p>",
